methods.name: distributeExcessAssets
methods.desc:
If someone deposits excess assets to the LP pool, addressExecutiveFee can either distribute them to the lp tokens or withdraw it, depending on the use case.
If someone sent there assets in fault, the withrawing can be use to return them back. If the pool received assets for example for having its algo stake online and recieved rewards it is prefered to distribute them to the current LP holders.

methods.name: calculateLiquidityD
methods.desc:
Calculates the liquidity  from the x - Asset A position and y - Asset B position
This method calculates discriminant - first part of the calculation.
It is divided so that the readonly method does not need to charge fees

args.name: x
args.desc: Asset A position balanced on the curve

args.name: y
args.desc: Asset B position balanced on the curve

args.name: priceMin
args.desc: Minimum price variable in base scale decimals (pa)

args.name: priceMax
args.desc: Maximum price variable in base scale decimals (pb)

args.name: priceMinSqrt
args.desc: sqrt(priceMin) in base scale decimals Variable pas

args.name: priceMaxSqrt
args.desc: sqrt(priceMax) in base scale decimals Variable pbs

returns.desc: Liquidity is constant in swapping each direction. On deposit the diff between the liquidity is number of LP tokens received by user.

args.name: priceMinSqrt

args.name: priceMaxSqrt

returns.desc: Amount of asset B to be given to the caller before fees. The result is in Base decimals (9)

methods.name: calculateAssetBDepositOnAssetADeposit
methods.desc:
Calculates how much asset B should be deposited when user deposit asset a and b.


On deposit min(calculateAssetBDepositOnAssetADeposit, calculateAssetADepositOnAssetBDeposit) should be considered for the real deposit and rest should be swapped or returned back to user

args.name: inAmountA
args.desc: Asset A amount in Base decimal representation

args.name: inAmountB
args.desc: Asset B amount in Base decimal representation

args.name: assetABalance
args.desc: Asset A balance. Variable ab, in base scale

args.name: assetBBalance
args.desc: Asset B balance. Variable bb, in base scale

returns.desc: Amount of asset B to be given to the caller before fees. The result is in Base decimals (9)

args.name: inAmountA

args.name: inAmountB

args.name: assetABalance
